.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-ACCOUNTING 5 "2026-04-20" "shorewall-nft 1.10.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-accounting \- traffic accounting rules for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I accounting
file defines packet/byte counters for specific traffic flows.  Each row
inserts a counting rule into a named accounting chain in the
.I inet shorewall
nft table.  Counter values are visible via
.B shorewall\-nft counters
and via the
.BR shorewalld (8)
Prometheus exporter.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/accounting
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
ACTION	yes	ACCEPT, DROP, or COUNT (count and continue)
CHAIN	yes	Accounting chain name to place the rule in
SOURCE	yes	Source address, zone:address, or CIDR
DEST	yes	Destination address, zone:address, or CIDR
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
DPORT	no	Destination port filter
SPORT	no	Source port filter
USER	no	User/group match
MARK	no	Packet mark match
IPSEC	no	IPSEC state (ipsec or !ipsec)
HEADERS	no	IPv6 extension header match
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Count all outbound HTTP/HTTPS traffic:
.RS
.nf
#ACTION  CHAIN     SOURCE  DEST  PROTO  DPORT
COUNT    accounting all     net   tcp    80,443
.fi
.RE
.PP
Count inbound traffic per source network:
.RS
.nf
COUNT    acct\-in   net:192.168.0.0/16   fw
COUNT    acct\-in   net:10.0.0.0/8       fw
.fi
.RE
.PP
Count ICMP for monitoring:
.RS
.nf
COUNT    icmp\-count  all   all   icmp
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewalld (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)

